        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> @chipsenkbeil Yes, I'm aware distant doesn't use TCP, but if I'm rewriting the start client logic to allow swapping out the uv_spawn, I'm going to also have it support TCP as that's required for certain servers. Maybe my original post was unclear in retrospect, I'm lumping anything that is not a `uv_spawn`'d server over stdio together.\r\n\r\nOkay, my misunderstanding :) I would just prefer to avoid writing too much special logic to handle LSPs within distant. For the most part, distant treats an LSP server like any other remote process and just acts as the bridge to forward stdin, stdout, and stderr back and forth. So if I can keep that functionality and plug it into neovim's `vim.lsp.start_client` in some way by providing an alternate version of spawning and pipes, I'm a happy camper!",
